Fix the scroll listener in `components/Navbar.tsx` for iOS Safari.

ROOT CAUSE: iOS Safari does not fire scroll events on `window` or `document`.
It fires scroll events on `document.documentElement` (the html element).
This is confirmed by debug overlay showing scrollY: - and scrolled: false on device.

Replace the entire useEffect scroll logic with this exact implementation:

  useEffect(() => {
    const getScrollY = (): number =>
      window.scrollY ??
      window.pageYOffset ??
      document.documentElement.scrollTop ??
      document.body.scrollTop ??
      0

    const handleScroll = () => {
      const y = getScrollY()
