Phase 1, Lesson 1: The Terminal
Before you touch a single JavaScript file, you need to be comfortable in the terminal. Here's why: the terminal is the native language of every server, every deployment pipeline, and every senior engineer's workflow. GUIs (click-based interfaces) hide what's actually happening. The terminal shows you the truth.
The Analogy
Think of your computer's file system like a building. Your Finder/File Explorer is the elevator — it takes you places but you don't really understand the building. The terminal is the blueprint and the stairs. You know exactly where you are, how you got there, and what's around you.
