What was fixed
The flicker root cause was a React dependency chain bug. Here's the exact chain that caused it:

fetchAssessment was a useCallback with [activeTabIndex] in its deps
Every 30s SWR poll → data object changes reference → triggers useEffect([data, isLoading, fetchAssessment])
Even though assessedKeyRef was supposed to block re-fetching, fetchAssessment itself was a new function reference every time activeTabIndex changed, making React think the effect needed to re-run

The fix was two-part: move activeTabIndex into a ref (activeTabIndexRef) so fetchAssessment has zero deps and stays stable, then replace the useEffect dependency on the whole data object with just data?.scannedAt — so the effect only fires when there's actually a new scan, not on every SWR reference update.
