Architect's Analysis of Your Vision
Before I write the prompt, here's what I'm actually building under the hood so you understand the decisions:
Transparent → floating solid requires two scroll thresholds and three visual states:

At top — full width, transparent, sits flush against page edge
Scrolled past ~80px — shrinks horizontally, gets mx-auto + rounded-2xl, gains solid background and shadow, appears to "float"

This is achieved with a scrolled boolean state, a useEffect scroll listener, and Tailwind's transition classes for smooth animation between states. The navbar wrapper gets different classes conditionally based on that boolean.

