This is the most dangerous one because it fails invisibly. When iOS Safari runs low on GPU memory (common on older iPhones), it silently aborts the backdrop-filter render pass, making the element completely transparent or invisible. The navbar disappears with zero error. The fix: remove backdrop-blur-sm entirely and use a solid or high-opacity color instead.

