# Fades & Facials — AI Agent Rules
# Stack: Next.js 16.2.4 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS v4, Supabase

## Coding Standards
- Break features into the smallest possible modular components. Never write monolithic files.
- File structure: UI components in `/components`, pages in `/app`, utilities in `/lib`.
- Build robust error handling on every feature. Use `try/catch` with exact terminal logging:
  `console.error('[context:functionName]', { error, relevantData })` — never swallow errors silently.
- No new packages without explicit instruction.
- Server Components by default — `"use client"` only when state or interactivity is required.
- No `tailwind.config.ts` — all design tokens in `globals.css` `@theme` block only.
- No `src/` directory — files live at the root of their respective directories.

## Context-Driven Commenting (STRICT — No Exceptions)
Comments explain WHY, never WHAT. Well-named code explains itself.

  CORRECT: `// iOS Safari intercepts touchstart as scroll — 250ms delay lets it resolve drag intent first`
  WRONG:   `// Add TouchSensor with delay`

  CORRECT: `// Anon client has no session cookie — pass the browser client so the bucket RLS sees auth.uid()`
  WRONG:   `// Pass supabase client to function`

Every major section MUST use this exact block format:
```
// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// SECTION: [name]
// WHAT: [one sentence]
// WHY: [one sentence]
// PHASE 4: [what changes when database is connected, or "No changes needed"]
// ─────────────────────────────────────────
```

## TODO.md Format (STRICT — Ticket Style)
All `TODO.md` entries must follow this exact structure. Never add a task without an exact file path.

```
### [STATUS] TICKET-XXX: Short descriptive title
**File:** `path/to/file.tsx:lineNumber`
**Issue:** One sentence describing the bug or gap.
**Fix:** One sentence describing the exact solution.
**Blocked-by:** TICKET-XXX  ← only if applicable
```

Valid statuses: `[BLOCKER]`, `[IN PROGRESS]`, `[BACKLOG]`

## Workflow Automation
- **Git Commits:** After a successful feature or fix, suggest a commit message following Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`).
- **Branching:** When building a new page or major feature, remind the user to branch first.

## Mobile-First Rules (Never Violate)
- Minimum 44×44px touch targets on all clickable elements.
- `touch-manipulation` class on all buttons and links.
- Every interactive element needs `onTouchEnd` with `e.preventDefault()`.
- All animations use `translate3d`/`scale3d` — never `translateX`/`scaleX`.
- No `backdrop-filter` or `backdrop-blur` — breaks iOS WebKit silently.
- No `opacity-0` for hidden state — use conditional DOM mounting.

## Database & Auth Rules
- Browser client: `createBrowserClient` from `@supabase/ssr` (in `"use client"` components).
- Server client: `createServerSupabaseClient()` from `@/lib/supabase` (in Server Components/Route Handlers).
- Middleware client: `createMiddlewareSupabaseClient()` from `@/lib/supabase` (in `middleware.ts` only).
- The module-level `supabase` singleton in `lib/supabase.ts` is anon-only — never use it for authenticated storage writes.
- Magic link only — no passwords.
</file>

